result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Repeater, Penalty - Operating While Under the Influence (4th w/in 5 yrs)] and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality, Penalty - Operating While Under the Influence (4th w/in 5 yrs)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Repeater, Penalty - Operating While Under the Influence (4th w/in 5 yrs)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality, Penalty - Operating While Under the Influence (4th w/in 5 yrs)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Megan Leathers was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Repeater, Penalty - Operating While Under the Influence (4th w/in 5 yrs)], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Fine/costs $2388.50 less $1500.00 bond posted to probation.

timeConds.notes:
Huber privileges subject to jail policies.  Sentence is consecutive to any other sentence.  If no sentence is being served, to commence forthwith.  May transfer to Oconto County.  7-31-2015 Judge George orders Oconto County Jail to release defendant to Cynthia Wettberg Sutrick on Sunday,August 2, 2015 at 8:00 am to go directly to her Memorial Service for her father, Michael James Playman, in Lake Delton WI.  She may wear street clothes to service.  Defendant shall travel only to Memorial Service and directly back to Jail and may not go to any other place.  Defendant may not drive any Mortor Vehicle or consume any alcohol beverage or any controlled substance during said stay and may not commit any violation of any law or ordianance.  Defendant must report back to Jail by 6 pm on August 2 in company of Cnythia Wettberg Sutrick.

8-11-2015 Judge Hepler revokes huber privileges and imposed loss of all good time.
